------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A license-aware, independent reimplementation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

wxNote is an independent, ground-up reimplementation of a Notepad++-style
editor built on wxWidgets + wxStyledTextCtrl (Scintilla) and Lexilla. It is NOT
a fork of, and contains no source code copied from, the Notepad++ application.

Notepad++ is used ONLY as:
  * a functional/behavioral reference (to match look-and-feel and command
    semantics), and
  * a test target (to compare behavior against).

No Notepad++ implementation code is reproduced in this project's own sources
(`src/`); the editor is original work. This mirrors the approach taken by other
clean reimplementations (e.g. DjvuNet relative to DjVuLibre): the reference
implementation informs and validates behavior, it is not a code dependency.

Notepad++ is a trademark of its respective owner. This project is not affiliated
with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Notepad++ or its authors. The UI uses the
wxNote name throughout; the app icon is the project's own SVG.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Licensing history (GPL, then permissive)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The project was GPL v3 from its start through v0.6.2. Every Notepad++-derived
file was replaced or clean-room-reimplemented over that time (icons, command
ids, plugin-ABI headers, themes, the default styler, three GPL lexers, and
finally the menu hierarchy itself), and the Notepad++-ABI reproduction was
moved out of the core entirely into the optional, separately-licensed
packages/npp-bridge module. With those engineering gates cleared, the core
relicensed to Apache-2.0 - solely to give users and downstream developers more
freedom, with NO commercial agenda. See LICENSING.md for the per-component
license record.

